{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-fill-in-the-blank-show-tsx","path":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-talk-about-past-experiences/task-31","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"title":"Vežba 31","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Poslušaj zvuk i dovrši rečenicu ispod.</p>\n</section>","instructions":"","explanation":"<section id=\"explanation\">\n<p>U negativnim pitanjima sa glagolom <span class=\"highlighted-text\">to be</span> u vremenu Simple Past, koristite strukturu <strong>Wasn't/Weren't + somo + kiambatisho?</strong></p>\n<p>Ovaj uzorak se često koristi za potvrđivanje činjenice ili pokazivanje iznenađenja ili sumnje. Na primer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Wasn't she at the meeting yesterday?</span> - Pita samo o njegovom prisustvu na sastanku, ali pokušava da to potvrdi jer misli da je bio.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Weren't they informed about the changes?</span> - Pokušava da potvrdi/proveri da li su bili obavešteni ili ne.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>U pitanju Lise, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Wasn't it stressful though?</span>, traži od Jamesa da potvrdi da li je situacija bila stresna, možda očekujući da jeste.</p>\n</section>","challengeType":22,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"b1-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-talk-about-past-experiences","lang":"en-US","fields":{"slug":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-talk-about-past-experiences/task-31"},"fillInTheBlank":{"sentence":"<p>BLANK it stressful though?</p>","blanks":[{"answer":"Wasn't","feedback":"<p>Ovo je oblik glagola <span class=\"highlighted-text\">to be</span> u Simple Past vremenu, ali u negativnoj formi. Ne zaboravi da napišeš veliko slovo na početku.</p>"}]},"inputType":null,"tests":[],"transcript":null,"scene":{"setup":{"background":"interview-room3.png","characters":[{"character":"Lisa","position":{"x":50,"y":15,"z":1.2},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"fi